		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Agile Unified Process</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Agile Unified Process</b> (AUP) is a simplified version of the <a href="/wiki/IBM_Rational_Unified_Process" title="IBM Rational Unified Process">IBM Rational Unified Process</a> (RUP) developed by <a href="/wiki/Scott_Ambler" title="Scott Ambler">Scott Ambler</a>. It describes a simple, easy to understand approach to developing business application software using agile techniques and concepts yet still remaining true to the RUP. The AUP applies agile techniques including test driven development (TDD), <a href="/wiki/Agile_Modeling" title="Agile Modeling">Agile Modeling</a>, agile change management, and <a href="/wiki/Database_refactoring" title="Database refactoring">database refactoring</a> to improve productivity.</p>
<p><br /></p>
